That&#39;s because hibernate wants to specify the model type. In this case you have 2 models and 1 DB table.

You could (postgres example):

    alter table users add dtype varchar(31) not null default &#39;Freelancer&#39;;
    alter table users alter column dtype drop default ;

Then you can build and deploy.

