The only way I am aware of this is to create a custom class implementing `Page&lt;T&gt;`. You can achieve it for the sake of simplicity by extending `PageImpl&lt;T&gt;` which implements all the methods for you.

Let the custom class ignore the getter to the `custom` field using `@JsonIgnore` and introduce your own one instead.

```java
public class CustomPage&lt;T&gt; extends PageImpl&lt;T&gt; implements Page&lt;T&gt; {

	public CustomPage(List&lt;T&gt; content) {
		super(content);
	}

	public List&lt;T&gt; getData() {
		return super.getContent();
	}

	@Override
	@JsonIgnore
	public List&lt;T&gt; getContent() {
		return super.getContent();
	}
}
```
